OL,3,CGorton and Denton to vote in by-
OL,4,Celection that could determine
OL,5,CStarmer's future
OL,7,FIn his final message to voters before
OL,8,Fpolls open, Sir Keir sought to woo
OL,9,Fwavering Labour voters by painting the
OL,10,Fcontest as a straight fight between
OL,11,Fhis party and Reform.
OL,13,FHe said: "The choice at today's by-
OL,14,Felection could not be more stark.
OL,15,FUnity or division. Driving down the
OL,16,Fcost of living with Labour or driving
OL,17,Fa wedge between communities under
OL,18,FReform. Moving forwards together, or
OL,19,Fopening up anger and division that
OL,20,Fholds our country back.
OL,26,@uD@JOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1772067789
OL,3,CGorton and Denton to vote in by-
OL,4,Celection that could determine
OL,5,CStarmer's future
OL,7,F"Reform's Matthew Goodwin thinks
OL,8,Fpeople who aren't white can't be
OL,9,FEnglish and wants women who choose not
OL,10,Fto have children to pay more tax. Vote
OL,11,FLabour in Gorton and Denton today to
OL,12,Fsend him and his toxic politics
OL,13,Fpacking."
OL,15,FLabour sources suggested the strategy
OL,16,Fwas working, claiming some voters had
OL,17,Ftaken down Green posters and said they
OL,18,Fwould back Ms Stogia.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@IO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/7
